# .secret-scan-allow — allowlist for the vendored secret guard (githooks/secret-scan.sh, KB.27).
# Lets legitimate fixtures / documented example keys through without weakening the patterns.
# This starter ships with NO active rules (every line below is a comment). Uncomment / add as needed.
#
# Syntax (one rule per line):
#   <ERE>          drop any matched line that matches this extended-regex
#   path:<glob>    exclude a git pathspec glob from the scan entirely
#   # comment      ignored (a trailing inline `# comment` after a rule is stripped too, so aligning is fine)
# Inline alternative: append the literal  secret-scan:allow  to the offending line in the source.
#
# Common examples (uncomment + adapt — keep matchable example keys OUT of this committed file):
# path:**/test/**               # test fixtures (be deliberate — real keys can hide in tests too)
# path:**/*Test.*               # *Test.java / *Test.swift fixture files
# <exact-fixture-string>        # an ERE dropping a known documented example key (e.g. an AWS *EXAMPLE id)
